Last Broadcast Date: Tue 21 Jun 2011
The peace campaigner who led a mass movement of women to end Liberia's bloody civil war and stripped off her clothes in a public protest, plus one little girl's experience of growing up below the breadline in the UK. Also, the playwright who worked his way from the slums of Miami to the Royal Shakespeare Company. Show less